# 01 - DTF and Checklist

I've created the Defender's Threat-Mesh Framework [https://github.com/MalasadaTech/defenders-threatmesh-framework/]. The Defender's ThreatMesh Framework is a tool designed to empower hunt analysts in uncovering additional adversary infrastructure. By pivoting on characteristics of known malicious infrastructure—such as domain name patterns, registration details, or network behaviors—this framework provides a structured approach to expand visibility into threat actors' operations. Inspired by MITRE ATT&CK, it focuses solely on discovery, offering pivot tactics and pivots to reveal hidden connections in the wild.
